<TITLE> NDI team meets Ghulam Quader </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 17 (bdnews24.com)  A team of the Washington D.C.-based based National Democratic Institute for >International Affairs (NDI) on Monday met with communication adviser Gholam Quader. The team led by former congressman and NDI board member Sam Jedenson, however, refused to talk to the media. The Communication officer of the communication ministry, Mofakkarul Islam said that the discussion had revolved round the forthcoming elections. "The team told the adviser that it will present an unbiased picture of the electoral atmosphere of Bangladesh to the world and the NDI will help Bangladesh in holding a free, fair and neutral election," Islam said. "The government is determined to hold the polls in time and all cooperation is being extended to the Election Commission," he added. The team from NDI, a nonprofit organisation working to strengthen and expand democracy worldwide, also included the regional director, national parliament member of Columbia and NDI's Bangladesh director. b
